      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EVERYBODY RISE (2) is a former NSW galloper immediately off the mark for the new yard taking care of a maiden field over 1000m at Sunshine Coast Poly. Was long overdue but strips even fitter and has form is soft and heavy ground. Can go on with it. A TOUCH FROM FAYT (6) was beaten 7 lengths when fifth in a 1100m contest at Ipswich three-and-a-half weeks ago. Long overdue but goes well heavy and course and distance. Gets chance. MOROCCAN WIND (4) is yet to recapture best form from first campaign, finishing out of the frame in two runs back. Jury out on the heavy but fitter and back and trip and has the ability for this line-up. I MISS MARGIE (3) was safely held last time when eighth over 1000m at this track. Drops in grade and has placed 2/3 heavy. Top-three prospect. SUPER DAISY (1) goes well fresh and can return with a strong run.",
